    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed at MRL 3. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels for every factor: Software QA (3≥2), Numerical code verification (2≥2), Discretization error (3≥2), Test conditions (2≥2), Output comparison (3≥2), Relevance of QoI (2≥2), Relevance of validation activities (2≥2), Numerical solver error (2≥2), Use error (2≥2), Model form (2≥2), Model inputs (3≥2), Test samples (2≥2), Equivalency of input parameters (2≥2). The Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification confirms prediction intervals are within the ±20% acceptance threshold. Sensitivity analysis identifies UHMWPE elastic modulus as the dominant uncertainty driver; targeted material characterisation has been performed to constrain this input. The validation dataset is representative of the COU operating envelope. No credibility gaps remain. The model is accepted for use in predicting peak tibial tray contact stress for Class II orthopaedic device design acceptance under the conditions defined in COU1.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
